Even 30fps on the RTX cards is really good becuase normally ray-traced scenes can't be done in real-time. Movies done with ray-tracing take hours or days per frame. Yes, this is most likely because of the higher resolution and sfx/gfx, but still, a ray-traced frame being rendered in 1/30 of a second is really impressive. You also have to keep in mind it was with an unfinished card, with unfinished drivers, with an unfinished game.

Also, wth Verizon

snippet.textDisplay:
All the people crying about the Twitch Prime removing the no ads benefit and saying there is no point to get the service now, are just spreading hyperbole. Does it suck that this benefit is being hidden behind a higher paywall, yes yes it does. Oh wait did another video not mention that it's being put behind a 8.99$ version of Twitch Prime instead. 

Also you still get free games with Twitch prime which is arguable the biggest benefit, you can stor your broadcasts for 60 days instead of only 14, (which isn't too helpful for just the viewers) and you can still pass on that 4.99 in the form of a free sub to a creator you like so essentially you get to sub to a person you like and you get free games for doing it.
Side note, if you really care about ads being a thing just fucking use an adblock
